hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Relevant equations:
$$\rho_b(t)=\frac{1}{6\pi G t^2},\quad r_{ta}=A(1-\cos\pi)=2A,\quad t_{ta}=B(\pi-\sin\pi)=\pi B,$$
$$A^3=GM\,B^2,\quad r_{vir}=\frac12r_{ta},\quad t_{vir}=\xi\,t_{ta}.$$
2. Virial density:
$$\rho_{vir}=\frac{M}{\frac{4}{3}\pi r_{vir}^3}
=\frac{M}{\frac{4}{3}\pi(\tfrac12r_{ta})^3}
=\frac{8M}{4\pi r_{ta}^3}
=\frac{6M}{\pi(2A)^3}
=\frac{6M}{8\pi A^3}
=\frac{3M}{4\pi A^3}.$$
Using $A^3=GM\,B^2$ gives
$$\rho_{vir}=\frac{3}{4\pi G B^2}.$$
3. Background density at virialization:
$$t_{vir}=\xi\,\pi B,\quad
\rho_b(t_{vir})=\frac{1}{6\pi G(\xi\pi B)^2}
=\frac{1}{6\pi^3 G\xi^2B^2}.$$
4. Virial overdensity:
$$\Delta_{vir}=\frac{\rho_{vir}}{\rho_b(t_{vir})}
=\frac{\frac{3}{4\pi G B^2}}{\frac{1}{6\pi^3G\xi^2B^2}}
=\frac{3}{4\pi G B^2}\cdot6\pi^3G\xi^2B^2
=\frac{18\pi^3\xi^2}{4\pi}
=\frac{9}{2}\pi^2\xi^2.$$
